{
  "doc_id": "19753",
  "text": "The purpose of the present study is to utilize fMRI to conduct a within-subject group analysis on 10 subjects with sensory conversion disorder in an attempt to better define the functional neuroanatomical correlates of sensory conversion symptomatology with a particular focus on the role of ancillary areas of activation. It should be noted that the raw data from the three subjects previously studied [CITATION_1] has been included in our ten subject group analysis.",
